The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 BRO clash with cops 

 Srinagar, July 20: Kargil police have arrested 40 Border Roads Organisation workers after they allegedly assaulted a team of cops investigating theft and illicit sale of construction materials meant for the national highway, reports our special correspondent. 

 Station house officer L. Shipa and some other policemen were injured in the alleged assault in Drass yesterday. The police have lodged four cases against the BRO men. 

 A source said there was a clash when the police party raided a site where the BRO men were allegedly selling construction materials to some people. 

 The army confirmed that there was a scuffle but said it did not know of any arrests. 




